# CANTO 28

<table data-align="center" data-cellpadding="10">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 100%" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td style="text-align: center;"><span class="small">ARGUMENT.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td style="text-align: center;"><span class="small"><em>To whatsoever evil tongue can tell<br />
Of womankind King Rodomont gives ear;<br />
Then journeys homeward; but that infidel<br />
Finds by the way a place he holds more dear.<br />
Here him new love inflames for Isabel;<br />
But so the wishes of the cavalier<br />
A friar impedes, who with that damsel wends,<br />
Him by a cruel death the felon ends.</em></span></td>
</tr>
